<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900925-0098</DOCNO><DOCID>900925-0098.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   Convex Computer Signs Pact</HL><DATE>09/25/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   CNX ESY</CO><IN>COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)</IN><LP>   RICHARDSON, Texas -- Convex Computer Corp. announced athree-year, $20 million contract with E-Systems Inc. ofDallas.   Convex will supply supercomputer equipment and services todefense contractor E-Systems for a computer data storagesystem called the E-Systems modular automated storage system,or Emass. Convex C2 supercomputers will act as the maincontrollers for Emass.</LP><TEXT>   Emass is composed of a Convex supercomputer with magneticdisks, a robotically controlled magnetic tape storagesubsystem and an operations console. Under the terms of theagreement, Convex will provide hardware and system softwareand will develop special interfaces that will be used withthe storage device.</TEXT></DOC>